## Goal

Extract all YouTube transcripts from ChromaDB, group them by topic similarity, and push grouped collections into NotebookLM notebooks to enrich our knowledge base and enable source-grounded Q&A across all ingested video content.

## Context

We have a large collection of YouTube video transcripts stored in ChromaDB. NotebookLM provides powerful source-grounded citation and synthesis capabilities. By grouping transcripts by similarity and creating topic-focused NotebookLM notebooks, we can:
- Enable deep Q&A across related video content
- Surface connections between videos on similar topics
- Build enriched knowledge layers on top of raw transcripts

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Query ChromaDB for all YouTube transcript documents
- [ ] Cluster/group transcripts by topic similarity (use embeddings distance or metadata tags)
- [ ] Create NotebookLM notebooks per topic cluster (e.g., "AI Agent Patterns", "Trading Strategies", "Developer Tooling")
- [ ] Upload grouped transcripts as sources to corresponding notebooks
- [ ] Document the notebook inventory and topic mappings
- [ ] Verify at least 3 notebooks can answer cross-video questions accurately

## Technical Approach

1. Query ChromaDB `youtube_transcripts` (or similar) collection for all documents
2. Use embedding similarity to cluster into 8-12 topic groups
3. For each group, use `notebooklm` CLI to create notebook and add sources
4. Track mapping in a reference file

## Artifacts

- NotebookLM notebooks (8-12 topic clusters)
- Mapping doc in `claude-vault/03-Knowledge/`
